modules.description: Handles HTTP request construction and representation, including payload formatting and authentication details. Works with structured data types for request bodies, headers, and credentials. Used to generate human-readable request logs and serialize request data for transmission.

Provides functions to extract and format response content, status codes, and headers, along with JSON parsing and success checking. Works with HTTP response objects containing body, status, and header data. Used to validate API responses and handle structured data from web requests.

Manages HTTP requests using a persistent TCP connection pool, supporting GET, POST, PUT, and DELETE methods with customizable parameters, headers, and authentication. Operates on session objects that track connection pools and request configurations. Used to efficiently handle multiple related API calls, such as batch data retrieval or sequential resource updates.

Provides functions for sending HTTP requests, handling responses, and managing headers and body data. Works with URL strings, HTTP methods, and structured data formats like JSON and form-encoded bodies. Used to interact with RESTful APIs, fetch remote resources, and submit data to web services.

handles HTTP request and response handling, including construction, serialization, and parsing of structured data, along with persistent connection management for efficient API interactions. It works with request objects containing method, headers, body, and credentials, and response objects with status, headers, and parsed content. Functions like get, post, and put allow for method-specific requests, while session-based operations enable batch or sequential API calls. Examples include generating authenticated requests, parsing JSON responses, and maintaining persistent connections for repeated interactions.
